How to Input in java ?

User defined input can be inserted by class which is present in util or utility package.
and here We can input the user defined input in Java by using some methods:-

class Scanner
   1- nextInt() = It takes integer number.
   2- nextFloat() = It takes floating point number.
   3- nextDouble() = It takes large Floating number.
   4- next() = It take one word String. Example:- Tarun is ,Output:- Tarun
   5- nextLine() = It takes multiple word string. Example:- Tarun is ,Output:- Tarun is
   6- nextByte() = It take byte number.
   7- nextShort() = It take small integer number.
   8- nextLong() = It take large integer number
   9- nextBoolean() = It take Bool value either true or False.
If we have to chech whether coming value is right data type is not then we have to write these methods:-
   10- hasNextInt() = If coming value is Integer then it gives True and if not then False.
   11- hasNextFloat() = If coming value is Float then it gives True and if not then False.

Let us take an example to see this documentation:-
Example 1:- ADD TWO NUMBER

import java.lang.*;
import java.util.*;

class inputKeyboard
{
  public static void main(String args[])
  {
    Scanner s=new Scanner(System.in);
     |        |       |       |
